 potatoes" title="New potatoes have thin, wispy skins and a crisp, waxy texture" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/new-potatoes">New potatoes</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">n-ew po-tate-oes</span><p>New potatoes have thin, wispy skins and a crisp, waxy texture. They are young potatoes andâ€¦</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="225g bag baby spinach">225g bag baby spinach</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="284ml carton single cream">284ml carton single cream</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="2 large eggs">2 large <a href="/glossary/egg" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--2 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">eggs</a><span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--2"><article id="node-252381" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/egg"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/eggs.jpg?itok=_1Q-Z6FA" width="100" height="100" alt="Eggs" title="The ultimate convenience food, eggs are powerhouses of nutrition, packed with protein and a range of 18 vitamins and minerals" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/egg">Egg</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">egg</span><p>The ultimate convenience food, eggs are powerhouses of nutrition, packed with protein and aâ€¦</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="50g freshly grated parmesan, plus 2 tbsp">50g freshly grated <a href="/glossary/parmesan" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--3 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">parmesan</a>, plus 2 tbsp<span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--3"><article id="node-259696" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/parmesan"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/parmesan.jpg?itok=Z34jTwkR" width="100" height="100" alt="Parmesan" title="Parmesan is a straw-coloured hard cheese with a natural yellow rind and rich, fruity flavour" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/parmesan">Parmesan</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">parm-ee-zan</span><p>Parmesan is a straw-coloured hard cheese with a natural yellow rind and rich, fruity flavour. Itâ€¦</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="10 anchovy fillets in olive oil, rinsed and drained">10 <a href="/glossary/anchovy" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--4 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">anchovy</a> fillets in olive oil, rinsed and drained<span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--4"><article id="node-257887" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/anchovy"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/anchovies.jpg?itok=-cVewjo6" width="100" height="100" alt="Anchovy" title="Anchovy" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/anchovy">Anchovy</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">ann-choe-vee</span><p>Silver, slender salty little fish found mainly around the Black Sea and the Pacific and Atlanticâ€¦</p> </article></span></li></ul></div></div> </section> <section id="recipe-method" class="responsive-tabs__pane"><h2 class="responsive-tabs__pane-title">Method</h2><div class="method"><ol class="method__list"><li class="method__item" itemprop="recipeInstructions"><p>Preheat the oven to fan 160C/ conventional180C/gas 4. Boil the potatoes in salted water for 6 minutes, drain and cool under the cold tap and thinly slice. Pierce the bag of spinach and microwave for 21â„2 minutes (or wilt in a pan with 2 tbsp water). When cool enough to handle, squeeze out the excess moisture and finely chop.</p></li><li class="method__item" itemprop="recipeInstructions"><p>Beat the cream, eggs and 50g/2oz cheese together in a large bowl. Chop half the anchovies and add to the bowl with the potatoes, spinach and plenty of black pepper. Pour into the pastry case (donâ€™t worry if it looks quite rough as this will add to the appearance later) and top with the whole anchovies and the remaining 2 tbsp of parmesan.</p></li><li class="method__item" itemprop="recipeInstructions"><p>Bake for 35-40 minutes until the mixture is set and the filling is just starting to turn golden. Allow to cool for a few minutes before removing from the tin. Serve warm or cold with a tomato and basil salad, or on its own as a starter.</p></li></ol></div> <footer class="recipe-info"><div class="recipe-info__publication">Recipe from Good Food magazine, <a href="/search/recipes/date/1059692400" class="text-style-alt">August 2003</a></div> <a class="recipe-info__magazine-ad" href=" https://www.buysubscriptions.com/print/bbc-good-food-magazine-subscription?promo=GFBS718&style=Brand&utm_medium=brandsite&utm_source=bbcgoodfood.com&utm_campaign=recipe_GFBS718_Brand&utm_content=recipe-banner" rel="external" onclick="Drupal.GFAnalytics.trackEvent(['Magazines', 'subscribe', 'Recipe' ])"> <img src="https://www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/magazine/gf_aug18_337x109.jpg" alt="BBC GoodFood Magazine" /> </a> </footer> </section></div></div>